ISBN 978-3-8055-9864-4

Each volume provides the organic chemist with an indispensable educational tool both for researching and browsing recent literature highlights in a way that is entirely complementary with searching electronic reaction databases. Extensive indexing and cross-referencing allows the series to grow, volume by volume, into an important reference work that deserves to be an integral part of any scientific library. Specifically, volume 78 comprises: Â· 546 graphical abstracts covering the mainstream organic chemistry literature to November 2010 Â· A summary of reviews covering the six-month period to April 2011, collated into easily-accessible sections Â· An informed commentary on research trends during the six-month period to June 2011
